<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>&quot;Cancel magic&quot; spell question</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Someone">Someone</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:33 p.m. 17/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> &quot;Cancel magic&quot; spell question<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Hail everybody! Let me present you some little story, then just say YES, or "NO", "BECAUSE....", thanks !

<P>Here we go:
<P>1) Your fiend is rooted and he has been buffed (magica shields on him). When you cast "Cancel Magic" on him, it will make him not rooted anymore, without cancelling his shields ??
<BR>YES/NO, BECAUSE....
<P>2) A necromancer (NPC/PC) cast fear on you, then one DOT, you have no magical shields on you... You must cast one "Cancel Magic" for the fear spell, then one "Cancel Magic" for the DOT.
<BR>YES/NO, BECAUSE...
<P>3) [a] A shaman (NPC/PC) cast a DOT on you, and you have 3 magical shields already active on you. You will have to cast 3 "cancel magic" to cancel your shields, then one "cancel magic" for the DOT
<BR>OR
<BR>[b] A shaman (NPC/PC) cast a DOT on you, and you have 3 magical shields already active on you. You can just left-clic the shieds' icons, then cast a "cancel magic for the DOT.
<BR>[c] A shaman (NPC/PC) cast a DOT on you, and you have 3 magical shields already active on you. Just cast a "cancle magic" and you are left without any shields and DOT !
<P>4) [a] A shaman (NPC/PC) cast a DOT on a friend, and he has 3 magical shields already active on him. You will have to cast 3 "cancel magic" to cancel his shields, then one "cancel magic" for the DOT
<BR>OR
<BR>[b] A shaman (NPC/PC) cast a DOT on a friend, and he has 3 magical shields already active on him. Just cast a "Cancel magic" and he is left without any shields and DOT on him !!
<P>Hehe, tanks for reading this message, and thx A LOT if you give me some answers ;)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
